videos.headline: Strickland stays on his feet and puts Syracuse ahead early
videos.description: Syracuse's Dontae Strickland catches the screen, breaks a tackle and runs 23 yards for the opening touchdown.

videos.headline: Feaster breaks free for 37-yard TD run
videos.description: Clemson's Tavien Feaster bursts through a hole and uses his speed to go 37 yards for a touchdown.

videos.headline: Spence shanks field goal way left
videos.description: Clemson's kicker Alex Spence hits an "ugly" kick wide left in the first quarter.

videos.headline: Philips left wide open for long Syracuse TD
videos.description: Clemson's secondary leaves Syracuse wide receiver Ervin Philips wide open down the seam of the field for an easy touchdown.

videos.headline: Clemson ties game with fumble return for TD
videos.description: Syracuse's Dontae Strickland coughs up the football and Clemson's Tanner Muse picks it up and returns it for a touchdown to tie the game in the second quarter.

videos.headline: Bryant taken down hard, needs help walking off field
videos.description: Clemson's QB Kelly Bryant is slammed to the turf as he tries to scramble near the end of the first half and has to be helped to the locker room.

videos.headline: Swinney says Syracuse outplayed Clemson in first half
videos.description: Clemson coach Dabo Swinney, disappointed in his team, says they need to improve almost everything.

videos.headline: Bryant goes down as Clemson trails at half
videos.description: No. 2 Clemson trails Syracuse 17-14 at the half. Kelly Bryant is injured at the end of the second quarter and has to be helped off the field.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Clemson-Syrcuse first half) 2017/10/13 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Renfrow makes great diving catch for first down
videos.description: Clemson wide receiver Hunter Renfrow makes spectacular diving catch along the sideline to set up a field goal.

videos.headline: Dungey breaks free for long run
videos.description: Syracuse QB Eric Dungey finds daylight and runs 45 yards into Clemson territory.

videos.headline: Dungey finds Ishmael for 30-yard TD strike
videos.description: Syracuse retakes the lead off a 30-yard touchdown pass from Eric Dungey to Steve Ishmael.

videos.headline: Etienne ties game with long TD run
videos.description: Clemson's Travis Etienne runs untouched for a 52-yard touchdown to even the score in the third quarter.

videos.headline: Clemson's fake punt fails in the fourth quarter
videos.description: Clemson attempts a fake punt, with punter Will Spiers' deep ball to Tanner Muse falling incomplete on fourth-and-6.

videos.headline: Babers says 'we never settle' after Syracuse beats No. 2 Clemson
videos.description: Syracuse coach Dino Babers and quarterback Eric Dungey reflect on the Orange's massive win at home over Clemson.

videos.headline: Brown: 'Everything that could have gone wrong for Clemson did'
videos.description: Dave LaMont and Mack Brown break down how Syracuse was able to pull off the upset win over Clemson.

videos.headline: Syracuse shocks defending champion Clemson
videos.description: The Tigers' perfect season and 11-game win streak are over after they fall to the Orange on the road.

videos.headline: Palmer on the biggest upset of the year
videos.description: Jesse Palmer breaks down No. 2 Clemson's 27-24 loss to Syracuse.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Palmer on the biggest upset of the year) SC Video 2017/10/13 ESHEET

videos.headline: Palmer surprised Bryant started
videos.description: Jesse Palmer discusses the injury to Clemson QB Kelly Bryant, wondering why he even played, with the offense looking stronger under backup QB Zerrick Cooper.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Palmer surprised Bryant started) SC Video 2017/10/13 ESHEET

videos.headline: Corso: 'Syracuse went right after Clemson'
videos.description: Lee Corso could tell after the first drive that Syracuse came ready to play and were hungry for the upset victory against No. 2 Clemson.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Corso: 'Syracuse went right after Clemson') 2017/10/14 CGD
